Aim
To develop a responsive navigation menu using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.

Algorithm
STEP 1 : Create the basic HTML structure using <nav>, <ul>, and <li> elements. 
STEP 2 : Add navigation links such as Home, About, Services, and Contact. 
STEP 3 : Use CSS flexbox to align navigation items. 
STEP 4 : Style the navigation bar with colors and fonts. 
STEP 5 : Apply media queries to detect smaller screen sizes. 
STEP 6 : Hide navigation links on small screens. 
STEP 7 : Display the hamburger menu icon for mobile view.
STEP 8 : Write JavaScript to toggle menu visibility. 
STEP 9 : Test the menu on different screen sizes.


<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Responsive Navigation Menu</title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">

    <style>
        /* Reset */
        * {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            box-sizing: border-box;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        }

        /* Navbar container */
        nav {
            background-color: #333;
            color: #fff;
            padding: 15px 20px;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
            align-items: center;
        }

        /* Logo */
        .logo {
            font-size: 22px;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        /* Navigation links */
        ul {
            list-style: none;
            display: flex;
        }

        ul li {
            margin-left: 20px;
        }

        ul li a {
            text-decoration: none;
            color: #fff;
            font-size: 16px;
        }

        ul li a:hover {
            color: #00c3ff;
        }

        /* Hamburger menu */
        .menu-toggle {
            display: none;
            font-size: 26px;
            cursor: pointer;
        } 

        /* Responsive styles */
        @media (max-width: 768px) {
            ul {
                position: absolute;
                top: 60px;
                left: 0;
                width: 100%;
                background-color: #333;
                flex-direction: column;
                display: none;
            }

            ul li {
                text-align: center;
                margin: 15px 0;
            }

            .menu-toggle {
                display: block;
            }

            ul.show {
                display: flex;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <nav>
        <div class="logo">MyApp</div>

        <div class="menu-toggle" onclick="toggleMenu()">
            â˜°
        </div>

        <ul id="nav-links">
            <li><a href="#">Home</a></li>
            <li><a href="#">About</a></li>
            <li><a href="#">Services</a></li>
            <li><a href="#">Contact</a></li>
        </ul>
    </nav>
    <script>
        function toggleMenu() {
            const navLinks = document.getElementById("nav-links");
            console.log(navLinks);
            navLinks.classList.toggle("show");
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
